On 1/29/06, Jonathan Cunningham <dawfun(-at-)seanet.com> wrote:
>
> So I got one of those new SVDA Mexican distributors from CIP, and got it
> all installed in my bus.  No workie.  After about three hours of diddling
> around with this and that, it turns out that the center of the
> rotor didn't touch the center of the cap.  The cap and rotor came
> installed on the distributor (both are brown).
> Has anyone else had issues with cap and rotor parts not really fitting
> correctly?  I got it to work by leaving off the dust-cover and puttingthe
> rotor on the shaft without pushing it down all the way.  The good news is
> that it works way better than the crusty DVDA I had before, but it sure was
> a waste of time getting it to actually fire off.
> Thanks to everyone who helped me figure out that a new distributor was
> probably going to fix by problems.
> Enjoy,
> Jonathan
